# Attendance Management System (HCI Project)

## Introduction
This project is a simple, user-friendly Attendance Management System designed for educational institutions. It follows Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) principles to ensure accessibility, usability, and a pleasant user experience for Admins, Teachers, and Students.

## Project Goals
- Make attendance management easy and fast
- Ensure the system is accessible to everyone
- Provide clear, attractive dashboards for all users
- Use simple language and intuitive design

## Key Features
- **Role-based Dashboards:** Separate views for Admin, Teacher, and Student
- **Easy Login:** Simple login page with password reset and show/hide options
- **Attendance Marking:** Teachers can mark attendance with a few clicks
- **Statistics:** Students see their attendance percentage and details
- **Admin Controls:** Admin can create users, assign teachers, enroll students, and view reports
- **Responsive Design:** Works on mobile, tablet, and desktop
- **Accessibility:** Keyboard navigation, color contrast, and focus management

## How to Use
1. **Login** with your username and password
2. **Admin:** Manage users, courses, sections, sessions, assignments, and view reports
3. **Teacher:** Mark attendance, view students, and attendance records
4. **Student:** View attendance stats, records, courses, and timetable

## HCI & Accessibility Features
- **Keyboard Accessible:** All forms, tables, and modals can be used with keyboard only
- **Clear Feedback:** Success and error messages are shown after every action
- **Color Coding:** Attendance status and statistics use color badges for quick understanding
- **Simple Language:** All instructions and labels are easy to read
- **Responsive Tables:** Tables scroll on small screens, no data is hidden
- **Focus Trap in Modals:** When a modal is open, focus stays inside until closed
- **Section Headers:** Clear, bold section headers for easy navigation

## User Guide (Quick Steps)
- **Admin:**
  - Create users, courses, sections, sessions
  - Assign teachers to courses
  - Enroll students in courses
  - Reset passwords
  - View reports
- **Teacher:**
  - Mark attendance for assigned courses
  - View attendance records
  - See student lists
- **Student:**
  - View overall and course-wise attendance
  - See detailed records and timetable

